---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const stories = [
  {
    name: 'Sarah T.',
    before: 'C5',
    after: 'A2',
    duration: '3 months',
    subject: 'O-Level English',
    quote: '"I used to dread comprehension passages. Now I actually enjoy pulling them apart — it\'s like solving a puzzle."',
    quoteAttr: '— Sarah T., Sec 4',
    paragraphs: [
      'When Sarah first joined A-Worthy, she struggled most with inference questions and summary writing. Her answers were vague and lacked the precision examiners look for. She would often write what she felt the passage meant rather than what the text actually supported.',
      'Through the SHARP Method, Sarah learned to treat every comprehension passage like a legal brief — identifying key claims, tracing the author\'s argument, and backing every answer with direct textual evidence. Her tutor worked with her weekly on structured annotation techniques that made even the trickiest inference questions approachable.',
      'By her third month, the transformation was unmistakable. Sarah\'s summary scores jumped from 4/8 to 7/8 consistently, and her overall English grade moved from C5 to A2. More importantly, she developed a confidence in analytical reading that carried over to her other subjects.'
    ],
    milestones: [
      { week: 'Week 2', text: 'Mastered Core Move technique for inference questions' },
      { week: 'Week 6', text: 'Summary scores improved from 4/8 to 7/8' },
      { week: 'Week 12', text: 'Achieved A2 in school preliminary examinations' }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: 'Marcus L.',
    before: 'D7',
    after: 'B3',
    duration: '4 months',
    subject: 'O-Level English',
    quote: '"My parents couldn\'t believe the change. I went from failing English to actually looking forward to the exam."',
    quoteAttr: '— Marcus L., Sec 4',
    paragraphs: [
      'Marcus came to A-Worthy with a D7 in English and very little confidence. His compositions were disorganised, his vocabulary limited, and he often ran out of time during exams. His parents were worried that English would pull down his entire L1R5 score.',
      'His tutor started by rebuilding Marcus\'s fundamentals: sentence construction, paragraph organisation, and time management. The SHARP Method gave Marcus a repeatable structure for both composition and comprehension — instead of staring at a blank page, he had a clear framework to follow every time.',
      'Over four months, Marcus progressed steadily. His compositions went from rambling narratives to tightly structured essays with clear topic sentences and supporting evidence. His reading speed improved as he learned to identify question types quickly. By the end, Marcus achieved a B3 — a jump of four grades that opened up his JC options.'
    ],
    milestones: [
      { week: 'Week 3', text: 'Built structured composition using CAPS planning framework' },
      { week: 'Week 8', text: 'Reading speed and comprehension accuracy doubled' },
      { week: 'Week 16', text: 'Jumped from D7 to B3 in O-Level English' }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: 'Priya K.',
    before: 'C6',
    after: 'A1',
    duration: '5 months',
    subject: 'O-Level English',
    quote: '"The SHARP Method didn\'t just help me in English — it changed how I think about every subject."',
    quoteAttr: '— Priya K., Sec 4',
    paragraphs: [
      'Priya was a diligent student who worked hard but couldn\'t seem to break past the C grade barrier. She understood the content but struggled to express her ideas with the sophistication that A-grade answers require. Her oral communication scores were also pulling her down.',
      'At A-Worthy, Priya\'s tutor identified that her main challenge was analytical depth. She would describe what a passage said but rarely explored why the author made specific choices. The SHARP Method taught her to evaluate language, tone, and rhetorical strategies — skills that transformed both her written and oral responses.',
      'The breakthrough came in month three when Priya scored her first A for a timed essay. From there, her confidence snowballed. She began volunteering for oral practice sessions, and her spoken English improved dramatically. By the O-Level exam, Priya achieved an A1 — the top grade — a result that surprised even her school teachers.'
    ],
    milestones: [
      { week: 'Week 4', text: 'Developed analytical vocabulary for language evaluation' },
      { week: 'Week 12', text: 'Scored first A grade in timed essay practice' },
      { week: 'Week 20', text: 'Achieved A1 in O-Level English examination' }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: 'Wei Jie C.',
    before: 'B4',
    after: 'A2',
    duration: '2 months',
    subject: 'O-Level English',
    quote: '"I was so close to an A but couldn\'t figure out what was missing. A-Worthy showed me exactly what examiners want."',
    quoteAttr: '— Wei Jie\'s mother',
    paragraphs: [
      'Wei Jie was already a competent English student with a B4, but his family felt he had the potential for a distinction. His school teachers praised his effort but couldn\'t pinpoint why his answers consistently fell just short of the A grade.',
      'His A-Worthy tutor quickly identified the gap: Wei Jie\'s answers were accurate but lacked the evaluative depth that distinguishes A-grade responses. He was answering what the text said but not engaging with how and why it was effective. Two targeted adjustments — adding evaluative commentary to comprehension answers and strengthening his essay conclusions — made an immediate difference.',
      'In just two months of focused work, Wei Jie\'s grades crossed the A threshold. His comprehension scores improved by 8 marks on average, and his compositions gained the analytical edge they had been missing. He achieved an A2 in the O-Level exam, proving that sometimes the difference between good and excellent is a matter of technique, not effort.'
    ],
    milestones: [
      { week: 'Week 1', text: 'Diagnostic identified evaluative depth as key gap' },
      { week: 'Week 4', text: 'Comprehension scores improved by 8 marks on average' },
      { week: 'Week 8', text: 'Achieved A2 — crossed into distinction territory' }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: 'Aisha M.',
    before: 'U',
    after: 'B',
    duration: '6 months',
    subject: 'H1 General Paper',
    quote: '"GP felt like a guessing game until A-Worthy. The frameworks made every question answerable — I always knew where to start."',
    quoteAttr: '— Aisha M., JC2',
    paragraphs: [
      'Aisha came to A-Worthy at the end of JC1 with a U for her promotional GP exam. She read widely, followed the news, and could speak intelligently about almost any issue — but on paper, her essays wandered, her counter-arguments were thin, and her AQ responses missed the mark every time.',
      'Her tutor diagnosed the issue in a single session: Aisha was thinking in points but not in arguments. The SHARP Method gave her a system. The P-E-E-L framework turned scattered ideas into structured paragraphs. The Evaluation Matrix forced her to consider counter-arguments before writing a single word. The AQ Response Template gave her a repeatable opening that no longer cost her marks.',
      'Over six months, Aisha rebuilt her GP from the ground up. She started keeping an argument bank organised by theme, practised one timed essay every week, and learned to mark her own work against the official Cambridge band descriptors. By the prelims, she was sitting at B. By the A-Level, she held the B — a four-grade jump that her school cohort was talking about for the rest of the year.'
    ],
    milestones: [
      { week: 'Week 2', text: 'Introduced to the P-E-E-L paragraph framework' },
      { week: 'Week 12', text: 'AQ scores crossed into Band 3 territory' },
      { week: 'Week 24', text: 'Achieved B in H1 General Paper at A-Level' }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: 'Daniel O.',
    before: 'U',
    after: 'A',
    duration: '8 months',
    subject: 'H2 Economics',
    quote: '"I went from blank-staring at case studies to actually enjoying them. The DEED structure changed everything for me."',
    quoteAttr: '— Daniel O., JC2',
    paragraphs: [
      'Daniel scored a U for H2 Economics in his JC1 promotional exam. He knew the theory — he could recite definitions and draw diagrams from memory — but his essays read like memorised textbook entries, and his case study answers ignored the data entirely. He was on the verge of dropping the subject.',
      'His A-Worthy tutor focused on application, not content. The DEED framework (Define, Explain, Evaluate, Diagram) gave Daniel a clear structure for every essay paragraph. The Extract-Link-Apply technique forced him to actually engage with case study data rather than write around it. And the diagram speed-drills at the start of every lesson turned his shaky AD-AS curves into precise, fully-labelled examiner-ready diagrams.',
      'Eight months later, Daniel walked out of his A-Level Economics paper with an A. More importantly, he applied to read Economics at NUS the following year — a path he would have ruled out the year before. The transformation wasn\'t about working harder; it was about working with a method that made the marks accessible.'
    ],
    milestones: [
      { week: 'Week 3', text: 'Mastered DEED essay structure for the first time' },
      { week: 'Week 16', text: 'Case study scores moved consistently into L3 band' },
      { week: 'Week 32', text: 'Achieved A in H2 Economics at A-Level' }
    ]
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Success Stories | A-Worthy Student Transformations" description="Real grade transformations from A-Worthy students across O-Level English & Maths, H1 GP & H2 Economics. The SHARP Method, six per class, every subject we teach.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <span class="eyebrow">Success Stories</span>
      <h1>Real students, real transformations</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Every grade improvement starts with the right method &mdash; the SHARP Method (See, Hit, Apply, Refine, Practise). Here are six students across O-Level English, H1 General Paper, and H2 Economics who proved it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== STORIES ===== -->
  <section class="section stories-section">
    <div class="container">
      {stories.map((story, i) => (
        <article class="story-card">
          <div class="story-header">
            <div class="story-grade-change">
              <span class="grade grade-before">{story.before}</span>
              <span class="grade-arrow" aria-label="to">
                <svg aria-hidden="true" width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
              </span>
              <span class="grade grade-after">{story.after}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="story-meta">
              <h2 class="story-name">{story.name}</h2>
              <span class="story-subject">{story.subject}</span>
              <span class="story-duration-badge">{story.duration}</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="story-body">
            {story.paragraphs.map((p: string) => (
              <p>{p}</p>
            ))}
          </div>

          <div class="story-timeline">
            <h3 class="timeline-heading">Key Milestones</h3>
            <div class="timeline">
              {story.milestones.map((m: { week: string; text: string }) => (
                <div class="timeline-item">
                  <span class="timeline-marker"></span>
                  <div class="timeline-content">
                    <span class="timeline-week">{m.week}</span>
                    <span class="timeline-text">{m.text}</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <blockquote class="story-quote">
            <p>{story.quote}</p>
            <cite>{story.quoteAttr}</cite>
          </blockquote>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CTA ===== -->
  <section class="section cta-section">
    <div class="container" style="text-align: center; max-width: 640px;">
      <span class="eyebrow">Your Turn</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Your child could be next</h2>
      <p class="cta-desc">Every success story started with a free diagnostic assessment. Book one today and discover your child&rsquo;s potential.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-accent plausible-event-name=CTA+Click">Book Free Assessment</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ===== HERO ===== */
  .hero {
    padding: 1.25rem 0 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
  }
  .hero-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--page-padding);
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 200;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ===== STORY CARDS ===== */
  .stories-section {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }
  .story-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius-lg);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    transition: border-color var(--transition-fast), box-shadow var(--transition-fast);
  }
  .story-card:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--color-accent-light);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 28px rgba(212, 133, 58, 0.1);
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .story-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 8px 28px rgba(224, 152, 80, 0.12);
  }
  .story-card:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .story-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .story-grade-change {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .grade {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 52px;
    height: 52px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .grade-before {
    background: rgba(220, 80, 80, 0.1);
    color: #c0392b;
    border: 1.5px solid rgba(220, 80, 80, 0.25);
  }
  .grade-after {
    background: rgba(39, 174, 96, 0.1);
    color: #27ae60;
    border: 1.5px solid rgba(39, 174, 96, 0.25);
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .grade-before {
    background: rgba(220, 80, 80, 0.15);
    color: #e74c3c;
    border-color: rgba(220, 80, 80, 0.3);
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .grade-after {
    background: rgba(39, 174, 96, 0.15);
    color: #2ecc71;
    border-color: rgba(39, 174, 96, 0.3);
  }
  .grade-arrow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .story-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }
  .story-name {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .story-subject {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .story-duration-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    width: fit-content;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background: rgba(212, 133, 58, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(212, 133, 58, 0.2);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* Body */
  .story-body p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .story-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .story-timeline {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }
  .timeline-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 5px;
    top: 4px;
    bottom: 4px;
    width: 1px;
    background: var(--border-color);
  }
  .timeline-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: -1.5rem;
    top: 6px;
    width: 11px;
    height: 11px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border: 2px solid var(--bg-primary);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .timeline-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.15rem;
  }
  .timeline-week {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
  .timeline-text {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Quote */
  .story-quote {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(43, 90, 140, 0.04);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--border-radius) var(--border-radius) 0;
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .story-quote {
    background: rgba(43, 90, 140, 0.08);
  }
  .story-quote p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .story-quote cite {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-section {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
  }
  .cta-desc {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .story-card {
      padding: 1rem;
    }
    .story-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .grade {
      width: 44px;
      height: 44px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .story-name {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
    .hero {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      padding-right: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
